    "699347": {
      "title": "23 s precursor ribosomal RNA of Rhodopseudomonas spheroides",
      "abstract": "The bulk RNA of Rhodopseudomonas spheroides fails to show 23 s RNA when examined by either sucrose gradient sedimentation or polyacrylamide gel electrophoresis. Careful extraction of RNA by any of several techniques reveals ribosomal RNA's of three molecular weights: 5.3 × 105, 4.2 × 105 and 3.6 × 104 daltons, as determined by mobility on polyacrylamide gels. The smaller ribosome subunit (29 s) contains 5.3 × 105 dalton RNA, and the larger subunit (45 s) contains 5.3 and 4.2 × 105 dalton RNA molecules. Pulse-labeling experiments show precursor ribosomal RNA molecules of 1.1 × 106 and 6.3 × 105 daltons. Since the pulse-labeled 1.1 × 106 molecule is found in sucrose gradients of whole-cell extracts in positions expected of 45 s ribonuleoprotein precursor particles, it is presumed to give rise to the two smaller RNA's found in the mature 45 s particle. The 6.3 × 105 dalton precursor RNA molecule probably gives rise to the RNA resident in the 29 s subunit."
